eJp-XwCNjxfxrZ6BJPfcPSg2l4Ecvmp3YdRBRwdR0GQNhLkZjcOh-3IyaQ_F251NqccZqAfG0vAOUG8uRKtyc-gZQKikGwuP-nk_sAJzTF5ue6YWUtfud5Kx_IKLE8_HjTxxt7gqj3PYBAX15857fKxxDaIE9BpIIOFAsvhC0_wxvRXgEC57Z4mYsFIQMMylKGDCOFz8OKXGh01FTk6DuMSr4GaWTT5o4I8YRp7IZzUKAfNk7W_N695PnFMIw18pBa7etbOq6fTmXs80MkUCZw08Kiq-OHZbTuwcI8JjBFSVaY7bnBdUzDSAXZ0sH9DDwbpPtLRarrAMvlWatKPkP6ldaxGWMKEFgIzFlr9LCiTPznFgCrMLALNciUaeLHiz7eI8ekPJ2AxJZl2kF3PX8WXqN2uOk7z4zWKttXOJdukAEPxVAHUBXapGkHrHqwxMm13NP8mNunnbPka7IzrZNUbYva_tNwLtGp8TqN1_SU1jcH8qUyA5ZX1h1U8VkiwWXQpiL4xjHINTMjaW7Xsr9Y-zo1NPkm9BsOnquCpMAe2JhcDxwd4ngk3MOmuMpMZyTKn2d6TgApQKcckA_FYq5p7m5anWCP3yJrzMfZxqJ7vXfJ0uNxeCNxBAqBZ6_03AZNZBZt4ib1IjsLbsJgmxkH5jn-EgX4jlDuhLRRGt3dIKqwcrSYSt0aT8IV8U9aXv0UV3RqO0hnL_TT-XFWxKzaGzv0UeqYnPXoocs5jn7qHOkx1EpDA_fF760Fui-vlu6QQfPfshq8-AZkrU37PEgKk-wpt85lZIUSHU=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test compilation**\\n\\nI'm considering how nativeTestCompile may be using agent metadata generated from javaTest. It seems in this repo, tests run natively using metadata in the metadata directory, not needing an agent. I wonder if I can use public non-test helper classes in the test file, but the metadata shouldn't include those. \\n\\nFor line 86, I know TCCL cannot load the target, but SecurityActions.class.getClassLoader can help. If the test target is the app class loader, well, I've confirmed that SecurityActions.class is loaded by the same app!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring new instance invocation**\\n\\nI need to invoke the overload method newInstance with parameters like String, Class<?>[], Object[], Class<T>, and ClassLoader. If I use an explicit ClassLoader to load the helper class, I also need to make sure the expectedType cast is correct. \\n\\nI’m considering using the interface Greeter and its implementation that includes public or private constructors. The constructor at line 161 happens in the newInstance call, and I need to guarantee using Constructor#newInstance along with getDeclaredConstructor. I'll define a helper class for this, but I’m curious about the implementation details.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test setup**\\n\\nI'm thinking I need to make sure to import AssertJ and JUnit for my test setup. There's also a mention of potentially needing to include `org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport` if I'm catching something, but I'd rather avoid that. I should ensure that my class names don’t include version numbers, and it looks like I’m aiming for a one-to-one mapping for my active class, \\\"SecurityActionsTest.\\\" I wonder if I need to remove any placeholders, although keeping coverage for the active class in its own Java test file sounds okay.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing methods**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I should add reachability metadata for SecurityActions methods. It feels like it could be specific to testing, which makes me hesitate. Maybe I should consider a direct compile dependency to the source through the package, but that doesn’t seem like the right approach either. I really need to think about how JUnit native image testing fits into this project. It's a bit of a puzzle!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how dynamic access is not active during tests. If I'm considering loadClass helpers, I might use `Class.forName` to test a class. Would metadata include a test helper? No, I don't think so. I need to think about whether catching unsupported dynamic class loading is necessary, but I might not need to. Perhaps I should create a test to handle unsupported cases, but since the class is known, maybe that's not needed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_lViJcDGvBMB0lkrSAR0Z4auh|fc_0db28ce5e89cdb9a0169f65258f25481a1b536df6c23d1a7e5", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jboss.arquillian.core/arquillian-core-spi/1.1.10.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_arquillian_core/arquillian_core_spi/SecurityActionsTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_jboss_arquillian_core.arquillian_core_spi;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class SecurityActionsTest {\n    private static final String SECURITY_ACTIONS_CLASS_NAME = \"org.jboss.arquillian.core.spi.SecurityActions\";\n\n    @Test\n    public void loadClassUsesThreadContextClassLoaderWhenAvailable() throws Exception {\n        Class<?> loadedClass = invokeLoadClass(SecurityActionsLoadClassTarget.class.getName());\n\n        assertThat(loadedClass).isSameAs(SecurityActionsLoadClassTarget.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void loadClassFallsBackToSecurityActionsClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        Thread currentThread = Thread.currentThread();\n        ClassLoader originalClassLoader = currentThread.getContextClassLoader();\n        String targetClassName = SecurityActionsFallbackLoadClassTarget.class.getName();\n        ClassLoader blockingClassLoader = new BlockingClassLoader(originalClassLoader, targetClassName);\n\n        try {\n            currentThread.setContextClassLoader(blockingClassLoader);\n\n            Class<?> loadedClass = invokeLoadClass(targetClassName);\n\n            assertThat(loadedClass).isSameAs(SecurityActionsFallbackLoadClassTarget.class);\n        } finally {\n            currentThread.setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void newInstanceWithDefaultLoaderCreatesTypedInstance() throws Exception {\n        SecurityActionsCreatedService service = invokeNewInstance(\n                SecurityActionsCreatedServiceImpl.class.getName(),\n                new Class<?>[] {String.class},\n         